                    <ab>Dum in Dei nomine civitate <placeName ref="#places/65">Papia</placeName> in
                        sacro palacio hubi domnus <persName key="#Emperor/king" ref="#people/21"
                            >Berengarius</persName>
                        <rs key="#Emperor/king">rex</rs> preerat, in <rs key="#Laubia/topia"
                            >laubia</rs> magiore ubi sub <persName key="#Emperor/king"
                            ref="#people/322">[Teu]derico</persName> dicitur, in iudicio resederent
                            <persName key="#Witness #Bishops" ref="#people/253">Iohannes</persName>
                        venerabilis <rs key="#Bishops">episcopus</rs> sancte <orgName
                            ref="#juridical_persons/220"><placeName ref="#places/65"
                                >Ticinensis</placeName> ecclesie</orgName> et <persName
                            key="#Witness #Bishops" ref="#people/78">Adelbertus</persName> sancte
                            <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/189"><placeName ref="#places/10"
                                >Bergomate</placeName> ecclesie</orgName> [missi ex hac causa] ab
                        ipso pri[n]cipe constit[uti], una cum domno <persName
                            key="#Witness #Archbishops" ref="#people/323">Aihone</persName>
                        <rs key="#Archbishops">archiepiscopo</rs> sancte <orgName
                            ref="#juridical_persons/221"><placeName ref="#places/147"
                                >Mediolanensis</placeName> ecclesie</orgName>, resedentibus cum eis
                            <persName key="#Witness #Bishops"><name ref="Petrus"
                            >Petrus</name></persName> et <persName key="#Witness #Bishops"><name
                                ref="Adalmannus">Adelmannus</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Bishops">episcopis</rs>, <persName key="#Witness #Count"><name
                                ref="Gunthardus">G[un]tardus</name></persName> et <persName
                            key="#Witness #Count"><name ref="Dido">Dido</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Count">comitibus</rs>, <persName key="#Witness #vassusOf"><name
                                ref="Gausus">Gausus</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#vassusOf">vassus</rs> domni regi[s.....]dus, <persName
                            key="#Witness #Judge"><name ref="Adelgrausus"
                            >Adelgrausus</name></persName>, <persName key="#Witness #Judge"><name
                                ref="Walpertus">Vualpertus</name></persName>, <persName
                            key="#Witness #Judge"><name ref="Adalbertus"
                            >Adelbertus</name></persName>, <persName key="#Witness #Judge"><name
                                ref="Farimundus">Farimundus</name></persName>, P[.......], <persName
                            key="#Witness #Judge"><name ref="Donumdei">Don[um]dei</name></persName>,
                            <persName key="#Witness #Judge"><name ref="Iohannes"
                            >Iohannes</name></persName>, item <persName key="#Witness #Judge"><name
                                ref="Iohannes">Iohannes</name></persName>, <persName
                            key="#Witness #Judge"><name ref="Stabilis">Stabilis</name></persName>,
                            <persName key="#Witness #Judge"><name ref="Thomas"
                            >Thomas</name></persName>, <persName key="#Witness #Judge"><name
                                ref="Leo">Leo</name></persName>, <persName key="#Witness #Judge"
                                ><name ref="Rofredus">Rotfredus</name></persName>, <persName
                            key="#Witness #Judge"><name ref="Ragifredus"
                            >Ragifredus</name></persName>, <persName key="#Witness #Judge"><name
                                ref="Adalgisus">Adelgisus</name></persName>, <persName
                            key="#Witness #Judge"><name ref="Gaidaldus">Gaidoaldus</name></persName>
                        et item <persName key="#Witness #Judge"><name ref="Ragifredus"
                                >Ragifredus</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Judge">iudices</rs> domni re[gi]s, <persName key="#Witness #Judge"
                                ><name ref="Audobaldus Mediolanensis">Aupaldus</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Judge">iudex</rs>
                        <placeName ref="#places/147">Mediolanensis</placeName>, <persName
                            key="#Witness #Notary"><name ref="Eribaldus"
                        >Aribaldus</name></persName>, <persName key="#Witness #Notary"><name
                                ref="Leopertus">Leopertus</name></persName> et <persName
                            key="#Witness #Notary"><name ref="Petrus de Papia"
                            >Petrus</name></persName> de civitate P[a]pia, <persName
                            key="#Witness #Notary"><name ref="Aribrandus de Blasonno"
                                >Ariprandus</name></persName> de <placeName>Blasonno</placeName>,
                            <persName key="#Witness #Notary"><name ref="Arialdus"
                            >Arialdus</name></persName> filius Tazo[nis..........]dus, <persName
                            key="#Witness #Notary"><name ref="Sicardus">Sihardus</name></persName>,
                            <persName key="#Witness #Notary"><name ref="Ildebertus"
                                >Ildebertus</name></persName> et <persName key="#Witness #Notary"
                                ><name ref="Giselbertus">Giselbertus</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Notary">notariis</rs> et reliqui multis; ibique eorum venerunt
                        presencia <persName key="#Abbots"><name ref="Gaidulfus"
                            >Gaidulfus</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Abbots">abba</rs>
                        <rs key="#Monasteries">monasterii</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Monasteries #Royal_slave" ref="#juridical_persons/95">Sancti
                            Christi confessoris Ambrosii</orgName> ubi eius sanctum quiesscit
                        corpus, situm [in] suburbium civitatis <placeName ref="#places/147"
                            >Mediolani</placeName> et <persName
                            key="#Judge #Advocatus_of_other_public_authorities"><name
                                ref="Boniprandus">Boniprandus</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Judge">iudex</rs> do[mni] regis [et <rs
                            key="#Advocatus_of_other_public_authorities">advocatus monaste]rii</rs>
                        Sancti Ambrosii, nec n[o]n <persName><name ref="Stefanus"
                            >Stefanus</name></persName>, <persName><name ref="Iohannes"
                                >Iohannes</name></persName>, item <persName><name ref="Iohannes"
                                >Iohannes</name></persName>, <persName><name ref="Lupus"
                                >Lupus</name></persName>, <persName><name ref="Ambrosius"
                                >Ambrosius</name></persName>, <persName><name ref="Lupus"
                                >Lupus</name></persName>, <persName><name ref="Befanius"
                                >Befanius</name></persName>, <persName><name ref="Theuderius"
                                >Teoderus</name></persName>, <persName><name ref="Ambrosius"
                                >Ambrosius</name></persName>, <persName><name ref="Ursus"
                                >Ursus</name></persName>, <persName><name ref="Rimolo"
                            >Rimolo</name></persName>, <persName><name ref="Iohannes"
                                >Iohannes</name></persName> et item <persName><name
                                ref="Iohannes de Civenna">Iohannes</name></persName> de <placeName
                            ref="#places/574"><geogName ref="#estates/2380"
                            >Ce[v]enna</geogName></placeName>, <persName><name ref="Priectus"
                                >Precto</name></persName>, <persName><name ref="Lupus"
                            >Lupus</name></persName>, <persName><name ref="Laurentius"
                                >Laurencius</name></persName>, <persName><name ref="Madrebertus"
                                >Madrevertus</name></persName>, <persName><name ref="Ursus"
                                >Ursus</name></persName> et <persName><name
                                ref="Ursacius de Madrunino">Ursaci[o]</name></persName> de loco
                                <placeName><geogName ref="#estates/2377"
                                    >Madronino</geogName></placeName>, <persName><name ref="Iohannes"
                                        >Iohannes</name></persName>, <persName><name
                                ref="Ursebertus">Ursevert[us</name></persName>, Petrus,
                                <persName><name ref="Dominicus">Dominicus</name></persName>,
                                <persName><name ref="Luvaldus">Luv]aldus</name></persName>,
                                <persName><name ref="Raginaldus">Raginaldus</name></persName> et
                        <persName><name ref="Ursus de Salvaniate"
                            >Ursus</name></persName> de <placeName><geogName ref="#estates/2376"
                            >Salvaniate</geogName></placeName>, <persName><name ref="Munaldus"
                                >Munaldus</name></persName>, <persName><name ref="Mauricius"
                                >Mauricio</name></persName>, Dominicus, <persName><name
                                ref="Iohannacis">Iohannace</name></persName>, <persName><name
                                    ref="Stevanacis">Stevanace</name></persName> et <persName><name ref="Laurentius"
                                        >Laurencius</name></persName> de
                                <placeName><geogName ref="#estates/2378"
                            >C[a]l[to]nico</geogName></placeName> locus qui dicitur <geogName
                            key="#Curtes" ref="#estates/260"><placeName ref="#places/573"
                                >Lem[onta]s</placeName></geogName> non longe a <rs key="#Lakes"
                            >L[a]cu [C]o[men]se</rs> intencionem [a]bentes. Dicebant ipsi Gaidulfus
                        ab[bas et Boniprandus a]dvocatus: Isti Stefanus, Lupus, Iohannes, item
                        Iohannes, Ambrosius, Lupus, Befanius, Teoderus, Ambrosius, Ursus, Rimolo,
                        Iohannes, item Iohannes de Cevenna abitantes non longe ad curte Sancti
                        Ambrosii que dicitur Lemuntas, Precto, Lupus, Laurencius, Ma[d]re[vertus,
                        ursus, Urs]acio resedentibus in Madronino, Iohannes, Ursevertus, Petrus,
                        Dominicus, Luvaldus, Raginaldus, Ursus abitantes loco Salvaniate, Munaldus,
                        Mauricio, Dominicus, Iohannace, Stefanace et Laurencius abitantes locus qui
                        dic[i]tur [Caltonico, isti] omnes <rs key="#Slave">servi</rs> cum lege esse
                        debent monasterii Sancti Ambrosii et curtis Lemontas, set nessimus qua
                        racionem se subtraere querant de servicio eiusdem monasterii et curtis et
                        dicant se <rs key="#Aldius">aldii</rs> esse. Unde iam ante os dies ad
                        racionem edo Gaidullfu[s abba et Boniprandus advocatus] eiusdem monasterii
                        presencia domni <persName key="#Missus_regis #Archbishops" ref="#people/333"
                            >Andrei</persName>
                        <rs key="#Archbishops">archiepiscopo</rs> et isti <persName
                            key="#Judge #Missus_regis"><name ref="Ragifredus"
                            >Ragifredi</name></persName> iudici, qui <rs key="#Missus_regis">missi
                            domni imperatoris</rs> erant, et iudicum seu relicorum stetimus, et ibi
                        eos in iudicio servi a parte eiusdem monasterii conquisivimus. Set dum ic in
                        palacio a domno et [iudice inquisiti dixissent ips]i aldii esse deberent et
                        non servi, dedi ego Boniprandus advocatus vuadiam eorum per iudices
                        recordatores aut noticiam probandum, qualiter iam ante [os] dies presencia
                        iam dictis domno Andrei archiepiscopi et isti Ragifredi [iudici non aldii
                        set serv]i eiusdem monasterii se manifestasent, et ipsi dederunt mihi
                        vuadiam de placitum, ecce nos parati et in presencia abemus noticiam
                        firmatam, qualiter isti omnes servi eiusdem monasterii et curtis Lemonta
                        esse manifestaverunt. [Ad hec responderunt ipsi Stefanu]s, Lupus, Iohannes,
                        item Iohannes, Lupus, Ambrosius, Befanius, Teoderus, Ambrosius, Ursus,
                        Rimolo, Iohannes, item Iohannes, Ursevertus, Petrus, Dominicus, Luvaldus,
                        Raginal[dua, Ursus, Munaldus, Mauricio, Dominicus, Ioha]nnace, Stefanace et
                        Laurencius: Vere, sicut vos Gaidulfus aba et Boniprandus advocatus dixistis,
                        ita per omnia actum est et taliter nobis per iudices recordatores aut
                        noticia ad probandum vuadiam dedisti, sicut […..........con]stitutum est
                        placitum per iudices recordatores aut noticiam a probandum et finem
                        legiptimam faciendum. Cum ipsi taliter egissent, fecerunt auditores ipsi
                        n[oticiam conscribi], que ut supra ipsi ab [ordine ostens]a et relecta,
                        continebatur in ea inter cetera, qualiter villa Bellano in laubia solarii
                        Sancti Ambrosii cu[rti]s ipsius i[n] iudicio presencia domni Andrei [sancte
                        Mediolanensis ecclesie archiepiscopi et Ragifredi iudicis sancri palatii
                        missi domni imperatori]s et […......no]biles omines intencionem abuisent
                        Gaidulfus aba monasterii Sancti Ambrosii et Adelricus notarius advocatus
                        ipsius [nec non L]upone, Stefa[nu]s, Ioh[annes,] i[tem Iohannes, Lupone,
                        Ambrosio, Lupone, Bevanio, Teodero, Ambrosio, Ursone et Rimolo germani,
                        Iohannes, item Iohannes de Civenn]a, Dagnolino, Prectone, Lupone,
                        Laurencionem, Madreverto, Ursone [et Ursacione de loco Madronino, Iohannes,
                        Urseverto, Petr]us, Dominicus, Lu[valdus, Raginaldus, Ursus de Selvaniate,
                        Munaldus, Mauritio, Magioriano, Dominicus, Iohannes, Stevanace et Laurentius
                        de Caltonico pago co dicitur Lemontas prope laco Comacino. Quesierunt ipsi
                        Gaidulfus abba et <persName
                            key="#Notary #Advocatus_of_other_public_authorities"><name
                                ref="Adalricus">Adelricus</name></persName> notarius et advocatus
                        ipsius monasterii qua] rencione de servicium eorum supradicti ominibus quod
                        [...se subtrahere vellent. Ad hec responderunt ipsi omines se esse servi]
                        eiusdem curtis Lemontes et [monasterii Sancti Ambrosii, eo quod...]</ab>
                </div>
            </div>
